tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated chloride level, which may suggest mild hyperchloremia. Renal function, glucose, and electrolytes are otherwise unremarkable. Clinical correlation is recommended to assess for possible causes such as dehydration, medication effects, or acid-base disturbances. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected.
